SUBURBAN REALTY COMPANY, INC., v. HOERNER et al. [No. 66,

October Term, 1950.]

Decided, per curiam, December 12, 1950.

*32The cause was argued before Marbury, C. J., and Delaplaine, Collins, Grason, Henderson and Markell, JJ.

J. Paul Schmidt, with whom were Leonard Weinberg, Weinberg & Green, Robert L. Mainen, and James C. L. Anderson on the brief, for the appellant. The Court declined to hear argument for the appellees. Jenifer & Jenifer and Bowie, Burke & Leonard on the brief, for the appellees. PER CURIAM.

It is ordered this 12th day of December, 1950, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland that the appeal in the above entitled case be, and the same is hereby dismissed with costs on the authority of Maas v. Maas, 165 Md. 342, 168 A. 607, and Evans v. Shiloh Baptist Church, 196 Md. 543, 77 A. 2d 160.
